        "content": "<p>Why does Forge add extensions <a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/structuredefinition-standards-status\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/structuredefinition-standards-status\">http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/structuredefinition-standards-status</a> and <a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/structuredefinition-normative-version\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/structuredefinition-normative-version\">http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/structuredefinition-normative-version</a> to every element in the differential?<br>\nWhy is this useful?</p>",
        "id": 196862470,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1588920120
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Other than the root element.)</p>",
        "id": 196862577,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1588920220
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it inherits them - open discussion on <a class=\"stream\" data-stream-id=\"179177\" href=\"/#narrow/stream/179177-conformance\">#conformance</a> right now</p>",
        "id": 196864332,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1588921967
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In Monday's Forge release we'll greatly reduce the number of those inheritances. We might even remove some that were previously introduced by Forge, where it's safe. <img alt=\":forge:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/10155/emoji/images/11736.png\" title=\"forge\"> </p>\n<p>Many of them came from every element being a child of Element which has those extensions. And I think the intermediate solution (before the FHIR spec can address the underlying 'what extension should be inherited' issue: <a href=\"#narrow/stream/179252-IG-creation/topic/Forge.20propagating.20normative.20flags\" title=\"#narrow/stream/179252-IG-creation/topic/Forge.20propagating.20normative.20flags\">thread 1</a>, <a href=\"#narrow/stream/179177-conformance/topic/Context.20for.20Normative.20Version/near/196794346\" title=\"#narrow/stream/179177-conformance/topic/Context.20for.20Normative.20Version/near/196794346\">thread 2</a>) is that we will no longer inherit extensions from the root element. But <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"221719\">@Abel Enthoven</span> can confirm.</p>",
        "id": 196903866,
        "sender_full_name": "Ward Weistra",
        "timestamp": 1588949098
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes I can confirm  <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"203235\">@Ward Weistra</span> , sorry for the delay :)</p>",
